{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"623","heading":"Establishment of a Federal Real Property Council","label":"623 Establishment of a Federal Real Property Council","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/stI/ch5/schVII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe date of enactment of this subchapter, referred to in subsec. (e)(1), (7), is the date of enactment of , which was approved .Pub. L. 114–318Dec. 16, 2016The Tennessee Valley Authority Act of 1933, referred to in subsec. (i)(4), is , , which is classified generally to chapter 12A (§ 831 et seq.) of Title 16, Conservation. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see and Tables.act May 18, 1933, ch. 3248 Stat. 58section 831 of Title 16","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Change of NameCommittee on Oversight and Government Reform of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Oversight and Reform of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 6, One Hundred Sixteenth Congress, . Committee on Oversight and Reform of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Oversight and Accountability of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 5, One Hundred Eighteenth Congress, .Jan. 9, 2019Jan. 9, 2023"],"amendments":["References in TextThe date of enactment of this subchapter, referred to in subsec. (e)(1), (7), is the date of enactment of , which was approved .Pub. L. 114–318Dec. 16, 2016The Tennessee Valley Authority Act of 1933, referred to in subsec. (i)(4), is , , which is classified generally to chapter 12A (§ 831 et seq.) of Title 16, Conservation. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see and Tables.act May 18, 1933, ch. 3248 Stat. 58section 831 of Title 16"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Establishment","label":"a .—Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is established a Federal Real Property Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Purpose","label":"b .—Purpose","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to develop guidance and ensure implementation of an efficient and effective real property management strategy;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to identify opportunities for the Federal Government to better manage property and assets of the Federal Government; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to reduce the costs of managing property of the Federal Government, including operations, maintenance, and security associated with Federal property.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Composition.—","label":"c Composition.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—In general","label":"1 .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the senior real property officers of each Federal agency;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Deputy Director for Management of the Office of Management and Budget;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Controller of the Office of Management and Budget;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F1%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other full-time or permanent part-time Federal officials or employees, as the Chairperson determines to be necessary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":".—Chairperson","label":"2 .—Chairperson","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Deputy Director for Management of the Office of Management and Budget shall serve as Chairperson of the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Executive director.—","label":"3 Executive director.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":".—In general","label":"A .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Chairperson shall designate an Executive Director to assist in carrying out the duties of the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":".—Qualifications","label":"B .—Qualifications","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"be appointed from among individuals who have substantial experience in the areas of commercial real estate and development, real property management, and Federal operations and management; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"hold no outside employment that may conflict with duties inherent to the position.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Meetings.—","label":"d Meetings.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—In general","label":"1 .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Council shall meet subject to the call of the Chairperson.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":".—Minimum","label":"2 .—Minimum","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Council shall meet not fewer than 4 times each year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Duties","label":"e .—Duties","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to enable Congress and heads of Federal agencies to track progress in the achievement of property management objectives on a Government-wide basis;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to improve the management of real property; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to allow for comparison of the performance of Federal agencies against industry and other public sector agencies;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop utilization rates consistent throughout each category of space, considering the diverse nature of the Federal portfolio and consistent with nongovernmental space use rates;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop a strategy to reduce the reliance of Federal agencies on leased space for long-term needs if ownership would be less costly;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide guidance on eliminating inefficiencies in the Federal leasing process;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"compile a list of field offices that are suitable for collocation with other property assets;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"research best practices regarding the use of public-private partnerships to manage properties and develop guidelines for the use of those partnerships in the management of Federal property; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F7%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a list of the remaining excess property that is real property, surplus property that is real property, and underutilized property of each Federal agency;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F7%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the progress of the Council toward developing guidance for Federal agencies to ensure that the assessment required under section 524(a)(11)(B) is carried out in a uniform manner;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F7%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the progress of Federal agencies toward achieving the goals established under section 524(a)(7);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F7%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if necessary, recommendations for legislation or statutory reforms that would further the goals of the Council, including streamlining the disposal of excess or underutilized real property; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fe%2F7%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a list of entities that are consulted under subsection (f).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":".—Consultation","label":"f .—Consultation","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"State, local, and tribal authorities, as appropriate, and other affected communities; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"commercial real estate and development;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"government management and operations;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"space planning;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"community development, including transportation and planning;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"historic preservation; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Ff%2F2%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"providing housing to the homeless population.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":".—Council Resources","label":"g .—Council Resources","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Director and the Administrator shall provide staffing, and administrative support for the Council, as appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":".—Access to Report","label":"h .—Access to Report","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/h/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fh%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/h/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fh%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/h/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t40/s623/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft40%2Fs623%2Fh%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Oversight and Government Reform of the House of Representatives;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","head